  "text": "MUT activity. In addition to macrolide antibiotics, nonantibiotic macrolide derivatives, such as the motilin receptor agonist idremcinal (EM 574) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , were also potent and selective inhibitors of KCNJ5 MUT (idremcinal IC 50 0.60 μM for KCNJ5 G151R and 1.99 μM for KCNJ5 L168R , no dose response for KCNJ5 WT ; Figure 2 and Table  1 ). Several other compounds with macrolide structures, including troleandomycin, josamycin, kitasamycin, oleandomycin, oligomycin C, rapamycin, spiramycin, dirithromycin, rondomycin, and natamycin, had little or no activity against KCNJ5 G151R in the primary screen (see Figure 2 for selected structures).",
